AVIAN INFLUENZA (76): SOUTH AFRICA (WESTERN CAPE), OSTRICH, LPAI H7N1, OIE
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 7 Oct 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID, weekly disease information 2014; 27(41) OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16235


Low pathogenic avian influenza (poultry), South Africa
-----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Oct 2014 from Dr Bothle Michael Modisane, Chief Director, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa.

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Aug 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Sep 2014
Report date: 7 Oct 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 11 Aug 2014
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical disease
Causal agent: Low pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H7N1
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (LPAI_H7N1_2014_001, Oudsthoorn, Western Cape Province
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Aug 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 58 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Commercial ostriches

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 3.45 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comment: Epidemiological and molecular investigations have shown that this outbreak is not related to the 2013 LPAI H7N1 outbreak that occurred in the Eastern Cape Province. Geographical coordinates have been adjusted to be less accurate to protect the privacy of owners, in accordance with legislative requirements. Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: H5 and H7 avian influenza in its low pathogenic form in poultry is a notifiable disease as per Chapter 10.4. on avian influenza of the Terrestrial Animal Health Code (2014).

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Agricultural Research Council - Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (ARC - OVI) (National laboratory) / Birds/polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 8 Sep 2014 / Positive
Deltamune (Private Laboratory) / Birds/polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 8 Sep 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[To see all LPAI outbreaks (H2N5, H7N1 and H7N7) reported from South Africa since the start of 2014, see OIE's interactive map at http://tinyurl.com/lgmp94p (click on the S. African cluster, zoom in).

Most outbreaks have been reported from Western Cape province.

For background information on the impact of these outbreaks, which have been recurring or continuing for several years, upon the once flourishing ostrich industry of South Africa, see a recent media report at http://tinyurl.com/nfmbxpq. - Mod.AS/CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2840382,179.]
